** The company **   
  
A new player in the finance sector has established themselves very quickly by
buying an established business. Technology and the customer experience is a
core plank of the new organization, so they are doing things right from day 1.  
  
** The role **   
  
They have have rapidly building & implementing a brand new technology
platform, ensuring it is secure & scalable, build their own internal DevOps
function/Cloud Engineering function and automate & deploying IaC.  
  
They are 100% Azure shop. .Net and Javascript are the languages of choice.
Mulesoft the key integration tool, Terraform the weapon of choice for IaC and
automation, and using an array of Azure toolets (AD, Serverless, DevOps,
Virtual Machine Scale Set & Availability Set, AKS, Service Bus, Firewalls,
Load Balancers.  
  
They have built a strong Azure team (currently a team of 7) but they want to
bring another person aboard. The team handle both cloud engineering & DevOps  
  
We're looking for someone well rounded: you can script, automate (Ansible or
Terraform), you know security, you know IaC and it's deployment, you knows
DevOps & know networking. You maybe have even spent time as a DevOps Engineer.
We also need a broad skillset across the Azure stack.  
  
We're also looking for someone friendly & easy to work with.  
  
** What's in for you **   

  * The chance to help build something big! 
  * Plenty of WFH flexibility (the company is based in Melbourne, but the work can be done anywhere on the Eastern Seaboard) 
  * Great technology (Azure, Terraform, Terraform, Mulesoft, React.js) & modern practices (Agile, DevOps) 
  * A very healthy salary of up to $150K base + super + bonus 
Probably the best Azure role in town. Apply now! No need for a cover letter.
Your CV will speak for itself.  
  
#LI-Greg

